{
  "stem": "3040.3",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they already have the escort.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They took us out from the jail and formed us in-- in-- in, you know, in five in a row, and we were walking the streets towards Plaszow.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When we came in inside the gates of-- of the Plaszow consolation camp, there were two very large holes dug, tremendous holes, like bigger than this house.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And we didn't know what this is all about.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The Lagerkommandant-- this-- I can tell you the name.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "This was Goeth, Amon Goeth, the-- the one who appears in He came out and told everybody-- not his helpers, of course, the Jewish policemen-- everybody to form a regular, you know, fall in-- in-- into five in a row.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And he was walking from one to one asking, what profession do you have?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He, Goeth himself, ask everybody.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I said, I'm a mechanic.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So here there was a segregation right there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Some people to the left, some people to the right, not-- not unlike in something Mengele used to do in-- in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I was selected to the-- to-- to the-- I don't remember whether it was the left or the right-- to one side.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It turned out that 67 people out of more than 300 in that whole group were selected to live.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the others had to undress, move towards the edge of these holes, and they were shot down.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We see.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We saw that.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And I was among the 67 that was-- that survived that massacre at this time.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Then I was integrated, of course, at Plaszow, and-- and I was put to work.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "First, I was working in the-- in the laundry.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
